HEADWORD: Making-iron
<hw>Mak"ing-i`ron</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A tool somewhat
like a chisel with a groove in it, used by calkers of ships to finish
the seams after the oakum has been driven in.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

